[Think Stats Chapter 4 Exercise 2](http://greenteapress.com/thinkstats2/html/thinkstats2005.html#toc41) (a random distribution)

Problem: use PMF and CDF to find if 1000 numbers from `np.random.random` are distributed uniformly  
Solution: generated sample, PMF, and CDF
```python
sample = np.random.random(1000)

pmf = thinkstats2.Pmf(sample)
thinkplot.Pmf(pmf, linewidth = 0.08)
thinkplot.Config(xlabel='Random sample', ylabel='PMF')
```
![PMF](data:image/png;base64,)

```python
cdf = thinkstats2.Cdf(sample)
thinkplot.Cdf(cdf)
thinkplot.Config(xlabel='Random', ylabel='CDF')
```
![CDF](data:image/png;base64,)

Conclusion: the CDF is a straight line. Therefore, the distribution of numbers generated from np.random.random is uniform.
